============================================================
SALESFORCE SECURITY MODEL
============================================================

Salesforce Security is divided into four levels.

1. Organization Level
2. Object Level
3. Field Level
4. Record Level

------------------------------------------------------------
1. Organization Level Security
------------------------------------------------------------

Purpose
- Controls who can log in to Salesforce.

Controlled By
- Login Hours
- Login IP Ranges
- Password Policies
- Session Settings
- Multi-Factor Authentication (MFA)

Example
User can log in only between 9:00 AM and 6:00 PM.

------------------------------------------------------------
2. Object Level Security
------------------------------------------------------------

Purpose
- Controls what actions a user can perform on an object.

Controlled By
- Profiles
- Permission Sets

Permissions

Create
Read
Edit
Delete
View All
Modify All

Example

Account Object

Read    ✔
Create  ✔
Edit    ✘
Delete  ✘

User can view Accounts but cannot edit or delete them.

------------------------------------------------------------
3. Field Level Security (FLS)
------------------------------------------------------------

Purpose
- Controls access to individual fields.

Controlled By
- Profiles
- Permission Sets

Permissions

Visible
Read Only
Hidden

Example

Salary__c

Admin      -> Visible + Editable
HR         -> Visible + Editable
Sales Rep  -> Hidden

Another Example

Phone

Admin      -> Editable
Sales      -> Read Only

------------------------------------------------------------
4. Record Level Security
------------------------------------------------------------

Purpose
- Controls which individual records a user can access.

Controlled By

1. Organization-Wide Defaults (OWD)
2. Role Hierarchy
3. Sharing Rules
4. Manual Sharing
5. Teams
6. Apex Managed Sharing
7. Restriction Rules

Example

There are 1000 Accounts.

Sales User A
Can see only 100 Accounts.

Sales User B
Can see only 80 Accounts.

Object permission allows access to Accounts,
but Record Level Security decides WHICH Accounts.

============================================================
PROFILE
============================================================

Definition

A Profile defines the baseline permissions for a user.

Every user must have exactly ONE Profile.

Profile Controls

- Object Permissions
- Field Permissions
- App Access
- Tab Visibility
- Record Type Access
- Login Hours
- Login IP Ranges
- System Permissions

Example

Sales Profile

Accounts      Read, Create
Contacts      Read
Leads         Read, Edit
Cases         No Access

============================================================
PERMISSION SET
============================================================

Definition

A Permission Set gives ADDITIONAL permissions.

It cannot remove permissions.

A user can have multiple Permission Sets.

Example

Profile

Account
Read Only

Permission Set

Account
Edit

Result

User can Edit Accounts.

Permission Set always adds permissions.

============================================================
PROFILE vs PERMISSION SET
============================================================

Profile
- Mandatory
- One per User
- Defines baseline permissions
- Can grant and restrict access

Permission Set
- Optional
- Multiple per User
- Adds extra permissions only
- Cannot reduce existing access

============================================================
OBJECT LEVEL SECURITY
============================================================

Permissions

Read
Create
Edit
Delete
View All
Modify All

Meaning

Read
Can view records.

Create
Can create records.

Edit
Can update records.

Delete
Can delete records.

View All
Can view every record of that object, ignoring sharing.

Modify All
Can edit/delete every record of that object, ignoring sharing.

============================================================
FIELD LEVEL SECURITY
============================================================

Three possibilities

Visible + Editable

Visible + Read Only

Hidden

Example

Annual Revenue

Admin
Editable

Sales
Read Only

Intern
Hidden

============================================================
INTERVIEW TIPS
============================================================

1. Every user must have exactly one Profile.
2. A user can have multiple Permission Sets.
3. Permission Sets can only grant access, never remove it.
4. Profiles and Permission Sets control Object and Field permissions.
5. Object access answers "What can the user do?"
6. Field access answers "Which fields can the user access?"
7. Record access answers "Which records can the user access?"
8. Login Hours and Login IP Ranges are controlled by Profiles.
9. View All ignores sharing for viewing records.
10. Modify All ignores sharing for viewing, editing, and deleting records.
